ZH: 我的朋友把我当成了家人。
EN: My friend treats me like family.
ZH: 请不要把我当成一个陌生人。
EN: Please don't treat me as a stranger.
ZH: 她把这件事当成一个机会来展示她的才华。
EN: She sees this as an opportunity to showcase her talent.
ZH: 不要把这个问题当成一个难题。
EN: Don't regard this issue as a difficult problem.
ZH: 他当成了自己生活的一部分。
EN: He considers it a part of his life.
ZH: 这个项目被当成创新的典范。
EN: This project is seen as an exemplar of innovation.
ZH: 他们将这座建筑物当成了一个历史遗迹。
EN: They treat this building as a historical relic.
ZH: 不要把工作当成生活的全部。
EN: Don't make work your whole life.
ZH: 这个饭馆的服务员把顾客当成宾客对待。
EN: The waiters at this restaurant treat customers as guests.
ZH: 我当成了你最好的朋友。
EN: I consider myself your best friend.
ZH: 他当成这个国家的未来之星。
EN: He is seen as the rising star of this country.
ZH: 她把这个问题当成了她的责任。
EN: She takes this issue as her responsibility.
ZH: 这次事件被当成一个警示。
EN: This incident is seen as a warning.
ZH: 我希望你能够当成我的导师。
EN: I hope you can be my mentor.
ZH: 当成你的学生是我的荣幸。
EN: It's my honor to be your student.
ZH: 健康应该当成一种生活态度。
EN: Health should be seen as a way of life.
ZH: 我们应该当成这次失败为一次教训。
EN: We should take this failure as a lesson.
ZH: 这次考试成绩被当成升职的标准。
EN: The test scores are considered as criteria for promotion.
ZH: 别把这个玩具当成一件普通产品。
EN: Don't treat this toy as an ordinary product.
ZH: 他把这本书当成一本宝藏。
EN: He considers this book a treasure.
ZH: 这个地方被当成信仰的圣地。
EN: This place is regarded as a holy site of belief.
